.TH ASUS-SCREEN-TOGGLE-LAUNCHER 1 "December 2025" "1.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
asus-screen-toggle-launcher \- Launcher for the Asus screen management agent
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B asus-screen-toggle-launcher
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B asus-screen-toggle-launcher
is a wrapper script that safely executes the user agent.
It checks if another instance is already running and ensures the environment is correctly set up for D-Bus communication and the display server.
.PP
This script is typically invoked automatically upon user login (via a .desktop file in autostart), but can also be run manually to restart the service after a crash or configuration change.
.SH FEATURES
1. Instance check (prevents duplicates).
2. Initialization of state files in ~/.local/state.
3. Execution of asus-user-agent.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR asus-user-agent (1),
.BR asus-screen-settings (1)
